17/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Doris Pack, the leader of the European Parliamentary Delegation for Southeast Europe, has said that the European Parliament should press the European Commission to launch talks on signing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) with Albania by year's end. 
Pack, who was attending the Stability Pact conference in Tirana, made the remarks Tuesday (15 October) after meeting with Foreign Affairs Minister Ilir Meta. 
Pack said that the deadline is realistic, as her visit convinced her that Albania on the right track. 
She also noted that this would be only the beginning and that Tirana still has a long way to go before it concludes negotiations. 
Meta expressed his appreciation for the efforts of the European Parliament to support Albania's EU integration. 
(ATA, Albanian News -- 16/10/02)
